node.text:
I decided to take a few days to think and let the facts of my injury sink in. To discuss the next steps with my team and the specialists that will be helping me with the recovery and rehabilitation. Now that I have a reasonably clear outline of what happens next I am feeling much better about it. I look at this time I will spend out of competition as an opportunity for me to revisit the basics of my sport and to work on some of the things that I have not prioritised in the past. There are plenty of positives to take out of this and I am looking forward to all the work that awaits me.  I have made the decision that I will be a better athlete after this injury, 100%.

I sat down with @wit.fitness to discuss this whole thing, explain how the injury happened and what the next steps look like. This video will be followed up with mini-series where insight is given into my daily life, the rehabilitation progress and of course the exciting projects I am working on with WIT. The first episode will drop shortly🎥

node.text: Yesterday I did a takeover on the @foodspring_athletics Instagram. It was a fairly packed day of all kinds of training, taking Moli to Dog school, doing a 🥵 wod with @bk_gudmundsson and then answering a bunch of questions that were sent in. If you wanted to see it but missed it, then don’t worry, because here it is. Enjoy.

On the menu in my second session yesterday there were all kinds of fun things like this 9 min EMOM for example🥵⁣
⁣
MIN 1-3 / 175 lbs⁣
2 push jerks + 1 split jerk⁣
⁣
MIN 4-6 / 180 lbs⁣
3 push jerks + 2 split jerks⁣
⁣
MIN 7-9 / 185 lbs⁣
4 push jerks + 3 split jerks⁣
⁣
Thankful to have the @WODProofapp band to buzz me into each minute so that I could fully relax between lifts and wait until it was time to go again. ⁣
⁣
I'm uploading this again now as the first time there was some music playing and the video was blocked for copyright reasons. Here it is muted🔇⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
_⁣

node.text:
In so many ways this is my favorite moment of my career so far and I remember it like it happened yesterday. Being at the @crossfitgames under the Friday night lights at the Tennis Stadium was a dream come true but at the same time an absolutely surreal experience for me. I was surrounded by many of the sports elite legends and I couldn’t help feeling a bit awestruck and out of place. It was during this event that I really realised that I was actually one of the competitors, not just someone who accidentally ended up there. 

I had tried the “Heavy DT" a few months earlier after I had seen @anniethorisdottir do it and post about it. I tried it and managed to improve her score by a few seconds so I knew that this workout was up my alley, but at the same time by looking at the field I was competing against the thought that I could actually win the event never crossed my mind. 

I was fairly calm heading into this event because there was no outside pressure. No thundering expectations on my shoulders. I was a rookie and I had a gameplan and I was just going to do the best I could. I managed to set a good pace fairly early and held on to the lead through much of the event. I had a belt on in case that my lower back would stiffen up, but then after three rounds I was just so pumped and motivated that without even thinking about it I ripped it off and threw it on the floor.

My family and friends sat right infront of my lane. They were waving the Icelandic flag and screaming their lungs out so I could see them and hear them the whole time I was doing the workout. To be able to pull off my first ever Crossfit Games event win in front of them made it even more special❤️ 

_
#crossfitgames #tennisstadium #heavydt

node.text:
It’s always good to finish a strength session with a little sweat 💦⁣
⁣
15 MINUTE EMOM⁣
1- 10-20 cal assult bike ⁣
2- 20 GHD SU⁣
3- 20 Chest 2 bar⁣
⁣
Using the @wodproofapp band to start the recording simplifies that process a lot and then it is great to be able to check the time every now and then during the workout so see where I am at. ⁣
⁣
⁣
_ _ _⁣
#EMOM #Crossfit #WODProof⁣

node.text:
In the future when I'll look back at the training camp for the 2020 @crossfitgames I think some of my fondest memories will be from the +1 hr drive over to BKG’s gym that I have done 2-3 times a week for the past month.
⁣
That special feeling of sitting in my T-roc R, listening to awesome music, thinking about things and gliding through various landscapes in all kinds of weather.⁣ is something that I will always remember.
⁣
Iceland, you inspire me🇮🇸⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
⁣
_⁣
@vwr @volkswagen_island #vwr #trocr #iceland #njarðvík #hveragerði #bíllinnminn #micoche #minbil #mavoiture #meinauto #crossfit #crossfitgames #thetrainingplan  #simmagym #crossfithengill

node.text:
After the 2019 Games I made a lot of changes to the way I approach pretty much everything in my life. One of the things I added to my daily routine at that time is CBD-based sport supplements. At first I was looking at CBD to help with relaxing and sleeping better which is definitely what happened but I also found that it made a real difference in helping my body rest and repair itself after an intense day of training. ⁣
⁣
Todayt I'm thrilled to announce that I have signed a brand ambassador contract with new and exciting CBD brand @championsandlegends. There I am joining a team of incredible athletes such as @pvellner, @thorbjornsson, @jhharrison92, @tommycaldwell and @adam.ondra and I look very much forward to be a part of this story.⁣
⁣
There's no silver bullet when it comes to athletic performance, but I believe the Champions and Legends lineup of highest quality full-spectrum CBD products can help athletes of all types with recovery, anxiety, sleep, pain management and a whole lot more. ⁣
⁣
#ChampionsandLegends #EliteAthletesAllWarriors⁣

Photo by Sara Sigmundsdóttir in Innerfight Hq. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: Mens tank from @wit.fitness ✂️ the Sara way 🤌🏻

Week 14 Post Surgery.

1. Starting to be able to do a lot of new things = Overthinking everything and being a bit paranoid that I will start compensating and sustaining a new Injury.

Solution: Book a trip to Dubai, work with my physio @mtm.online. 

2. Realising that I am actually not competing at the Crossfit Games this year and seeing everybody getting ready = feeling sad and experiencing a horrible FOMO.

Solution: Spend a lot of time with my other half in Dubai. Book a trip to Dubai.

Took a random decision a week ago to book a trip to Dubai to get some work done and also reunite with my best friend @carmenbosmans. Man was it good to travel again after 17 months in the land of Ice and snow.

node.text:
I’m very happy to announce that I have ✍🏼 a new ambassador contract with @foodspring_athletics which has been my #1 resource for nutritional supplements, vitamins and more since 2017. A great brand that produces a wide variety of products that are an integral part of my everyday nutrition. 

Me and @bk_gudmundsson both signed with Foodspring at around the same time back then so it was fitting that we’d both extend at the same time now. I even tried using his back as a table for signing since we were training when the contracts arrived, but that was easier said than done👶🏻👧🏼

📸 @snorribjorns
_
#extended #teamfoodspringathletics

node.text:
Who says legs can’t be fabulous with a few scars = scabulous.

I have been using this stuff on my knee every single day. This is the @championsandlegends Recover roll-on gel which contains full-spectrum CBD, menthol and then a bunch of botanical extracts. It helps reduce swelling, inflammation and pain and then I just love the menthol smell and sensation it brings💆🏼‍♀️

📸 @snorribjorns

The SIGMUNDSDÓTTIR X WIT line launches in a few weeks🔥

You can sign up to get sneak peaks and exclusive access to it via the link in my bio. In a few days I will invite 5 people from the list to join me and the design team at @wit.fitness on a on a video call as we go through the final samples. You'll get an exclusive first look at the collection AND see what designs we are working on for next year. I can't wait to see what you think of it! 

The design process started in november and it is something I have enjoyed way more that I could ever have imagined. I have learned so much during this time and to be working with such a talented and motivated group of designers has definitely unlocked some creative sparks within me that I didn’t know where there. Now that we are so close to launching the line sincerely I hope that all of you will love it as much as I do. 

Hit the 🔗 in my bio to sign up
